cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with building instance segmentation using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN). Additionally, the use of Active Contour Models (ACM) and geometric properties of buildings suggest that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The end-to-end training approach and incorporation of priors and constraints also suggest that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the use of structured output models and evaluation on challenging datasets suggest that it may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
